\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Mermin2007,inun.423549119950101"

\end_inset

 will give a probability on the state space, and conversely Gleason's theorem
 implies any probability corresponds to a state in CQT.
 In another word, the Born rule can be deduced by a set of abstract definitions,
 axioms, and Gleason's theorem.
 Because the measurement process and Gleason's theorem are so related to
 each other, their DQT version will be discussed in pair in each 
\family roman
attempt 
